Cell["\<\
Symmetry relations play an important role in the theory of NMR.  Coherence \
selection rules, phase cycling, recoupling sequences, long-lived spin states, \
etc. may be rationalised by utilising underlying symmetry relations.

The mathematical machinery to describe the symmetry relations of a given \
object is given by a symmetry group. A symmetry group consists of all \
transformations (geometric or abstract) under which the object remains \
invariant. Consider for example the equilateral triangles shown below:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.728220896380918*^9, 3.728221063488654*^9}, {
