Cell[TextData[{
 "The water molecule is symmetric with respect to a reflection (\[Sigma]) \
around the oxygen atom and the trivial operation of doing nothing (e). The \
symmetry group of the water is thus given by just two elements:\n\n",
 StyleBox["G={e, \[Sigma]}.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\nWith respect to an appropriate basis we may assign molecular \
coordinates to the hydrogen atoms:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["H", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"e16c62b3-67c0-4ec8-a1f0-e8aeacdb70ae"],
 StyleBox[" = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"-", 
       SubscriptBox["r", "HH"]}], "/", "2"}], ",", "0"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"1039fb1c-c405-4c30-b2cb-8e9b372f4334"],
 StyleBox["); ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["H", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"119a669f-c878-49da-bf7f-e8afaaaaf2cc"],
 StyleBox[" = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"+", 
       SubscriptBox["r", "HH"]}], "/", "2"}], ",", "0"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"454b29e6-2673-4fc8-a026-1e956c31036f"],
 StyleBox[") ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\nThe symmetry elements of ",
 StyleBox["G",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " may then be represented as matrices:\n\n",
 StyleBox["e = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  TagBox[
   RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
      {"1", "0"},
      {"0", "1"}
     },
     GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
     GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
          Offset[0.7]}, 
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
         Offset[0.2], {
          Offset[0.4]}, 
         Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
   Function[BoxForm`e$, 
    MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.852284709926701*^9, 3.852284713174992*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"01cddb41-bedf-40d0-9840-5d80f52e8e52"],
 " ",
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "and",
 StyleBox[" \[Sigma] = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  TagBox[
   RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
      {"0", 
       RowBox[{"-", "1"}]},
      {
       RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "0"}
     },
     GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
     GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
          Offset[0.7]}, 
         Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
         Offset[0.2], {
          Offset[0.4]}, 
         Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}],
   Function[BoxForm`e$, 
    MatrixForm[BoxForm`e$]]]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.852284709926701*^9, 3.852284713174992*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"e6100420-aac8-4e1a-bd2c-aacaec1da4d6"],
 "\n\nThe choice of our basis has been more or less \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]arbitrary\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] without any special \
considerations. The idea of symmetry adapted linear combinations (SALC) is to \
explicitly take the symmetry of a system into account when constructing a set \
of basis states. For the hydrogens of the water molecule a more natural \
choice for the coordinate bases is given by the following SALC\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"c6ef6eb8-e7d1-489c-be63-5ccd36fd8686"],
 StyleBox["= ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"fbf770e7-9776-4d2e-a31a-77be1c92e677"],
 StyleBox["(1,1);  ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"56687efd-87b6-4091-a8c6-1e820a35f408"],
 StyleBox["= ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"cb07ac7e-3d1e-4d30-b2f6-8a5337bbe319"],
 StyleBox["(1,-1) \n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "These states explicitly take the symmetry of the hydrogen arrangement into \
account and may be used to define a basis transformation matrix that takes \
the system into a ",
 StyleBox["symmetry adapted basis",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ":\n",
 StyleBox["\n\[CapitalPhi] = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    StyleBox["(",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], 
    RowBox[{
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "1"],
      TraditionalForm], 
     StyleBox[",",
      FontWeight->"Bold"], 
     FormBox[
      SubscriptBox["\[Phi]", "2"],
      TraditionalForm]}], 
    StyleBox[")",
     FontWeight->"Bold"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"fd04b67b-7ce0-4a91-b8b7-cf244a218cfe"],
 StyleBox["\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   StyleBox[
    RowBox[{
     OverscriptBox["e", "~"], " "}],
    FontWeight->"Bold"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"51e6babe-da79-4eb0-98b0-1a2796d350f5"],
 StyleBox["= ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalPhi]e\[CapitalPhi]", "T"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"1613721f-5bde-457c-876e-8952b722dd79"],
 StyleBox[" = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {"1", "0"},
     {"0", "1"}
    },
    GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
    GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
         Offset[0.7]}, 
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
        Offset[0.2], {
         Offset[0.4]}, 
        Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.852284709926701*^9, 3.852284713174992*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"1ea40776-4373-452d-afd8-ec1ef6ca2884"],
 StyleBox[" and ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "~"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"8b6d73ac-6afc-48b8-b53e-b8a4568d4737"],
 StyleBox[" = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[CapitalPhi]\[Sigma]\[CapitalPhi]", "T"], 
   TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"ad77aaf8-d257-43d5-8199-b1b1c6c5aca3"],
 StyleBox[" = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"(", "\[NoBreak]", GridBox[{
     {
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}], "0"},
     {"0", "1"}
    },
    GridBoxAlignment->{"Columns" -> {{Center}}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}},
    GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
         Offset[0.7]}, 
        Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "Rows" -> {
        Offset[0.2], {
         Offset[0.4]}, 
        Offset[0.2]}}], "\[NoBreak]", ")"}]],
  CellChangeTimes->{{3.852284709926701*^9, 3.852284713174992*^9}},
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"8860c6b7-0805-497d-ba9f-0da84788d4ca"],
 "\n\nThe action (or effect) of the symmetry operations has been considerably \
simplified, multiplication of any vector by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["e", "~"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"af5b518c-40b9-4558-8f25-74c74e5ba804"],
 " or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   OverscriptBox["\[Sigma]", "~"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"6dcc9034-635d-402a-95ed-330f21f3dd36"],
 " has been reduced to simply multiplying the elements of the vector by \
either (+1) or (-1). \n\nThis is the general idea of a ",
 StyleBox["symmetry adapted basis",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", by taking the symmetries of the system explicitly into account the action \
of a symmetry operation may considerably reduced making the problem more \
tractable."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.728220896380918*^9, 3.728221063488654*^9}, {
   3.7282211222267337`*^9, 3.728221130577482*^9}, {3.7282211686435347`*^9, 
   3.728221248183666*^9}, {3.728221349247451*^9, 3.7282214691937075`*^9}, {
