Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["Lie Algebras",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588074747297937*^9, 3.58807475427406*^9}, 
   3.681107655503767*^9, {3.681108144544858*^9, 3.6811081457025437`*^9}, {
   3.728222855607125*^9, 3.72822285863028*^9}, {3.852186464306465*^9, 
   3.8521864668422637`*^9}, {3.852195029179085*^9, 3.8521950330348043`*^9}, {
   3.85219506479504*^9, 3.8521950742994037`*^9}, {3.852200032949952*^9, 
   3.85220003569989*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5743c81b-b9a0-4051-9ba8-\
80e191eb5f7e"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell[TextData[StyleBox["background",
 FontWeight->"Bold"]], "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.588074747297937*^9, 3.58807475427406*^9}, 
   3.681107655503767*^9, {3.681108144544858*^9, 3.6811081457025437`*^9}, {
   3.728222855607125*^9, 3.72822285863028*^9}, {3.852186464306465*^9, 
   3.8521864668422637`*^9}, {3.852193965900177*^9, 
   3.8521939668995667`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"54ac7436-e2b2-438b-ae6f-\
31297ee9b153"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Loosely speaking a Lie algebra is a vector space with some \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]additional\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] structure. Consider \
for example our three-dimensional space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"3bf29f99-5c8c-4304-835e-fcfab81d0817"],
 ", the standard basis vectors are \n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["e", "1"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"8f620e0a-5260-4ec9-bdf3-63631b90bb09"],
 StyleBox[" = (1, 0, 0) \n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["e", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"99b9ac59-111c-4a42-aaad-f84625f33c4b"],
 StyleBox[" = (0, 1, 0)\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["e", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"4fef231a-5157-4602-8684-645ee576add1"],
 StyleBox[" = (0, 0, 1)\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "Any vector in  ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Plain",ExpressionUUID->
  "9c9f8999-c428-40bf-ac43-cd86684e5c5b"],
 " may be expressed as a linear combination of these basis vectors\n\n",
 StyleBox["v = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "j"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"13476b09-c92c-47a5-a0f6-0fb048890ca8"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "j"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"68711c57-d46a-4771-b84c-4af339de2474"],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["e", "j"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"d038141a-8d50-473e-9993-c11b740cae1a"],
 "\n\nThe dot product gives a natural way to extract the coordinates of any \
vector ",
 StyleBox["v\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", 
    SubscriptBox["e", "j"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"9f784aea-7940-4756-9ba4-f6c380bd273e"],
 StyleBox["|v\[RightAngleBracket] = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["x", "j"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"eb765349-d529-4ee8-880d-ea03bab051d5"],
 "\n\nMathematically speaking the dot product takes two vectors as an input \
and returns a number:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[LeftAngleBracket]", "\[CenterDot]"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"cb007e3d-5c12-42b9-8ca4-a2781573334c"],
 StyleBox["|\[CenterDot]\[RightAngleBracket] :  ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"220dbc08-4e13-44e7-9971-04bc8e0fd7f1"],
 StyleBox[" \[Times] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"0b810560-e0b0-4333-910a-9413948ae807"],
 StyleBox[" \[Rule] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9ac0580f-1805-47b2-9788-001053ca5664"],
 "\n\nBut what about operations that take two vectors in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"e781def7-bf2f-4e49-8f25-e516cef4039c"],
 " and generate a new vector in ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"6df1c972-d3ec-4686-8134-459eedef931c"],
 "? Perhaps the most familiar operation capable of such a transformation is \
the three-dimensional cross product.\n\n",
 StyleBox["v \[Times] w = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"(", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["v", "2"], 
      SubscriptBox["w", "3"]}], "-"}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"0407f9cb-aee9-4bce-b25f-67c8ae579a77"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["v", "3"], 
    SubscriptBox["w", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"f3a9864a-4c99-4624-bcde-5ad0fa04fe10"],
 StyleBox[", ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["v", "3"], 
     SubscriptBox["w", "1"]}], "-"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"4a872325-6da1-49d1-bc85-1d95af414585"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["v", "1"], 
    SubscriptBox["w", "3"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"fa510946-a13b-4f39-ab15-d8a263484dfc"],
 StyleBox[", ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["v", "1"], 
     SubscriptBox["w", "2"]}], "-"}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"b3aaff31-e5f6-4dd0-b052-e65a6f278771"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["v", "2"], 
    SubscriptBox["w", "1"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"982830b8-a4a8-4474-966a-b121f0762fe4"],
 StyleBox[")\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "Mathematically speaking the cross product is of the following type:\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[CenterDot]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"bf33b579-16cb-4088-8442-873fd2e1ffa1"],
 " \[Times] ",
 StyleBox["\[CenterDot] :  ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"00a621c7-1e6d-4548-be06-e9bda9d8644d"],
 StyleBox[" \[Times] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"712e34ab-917b-49f3-83bb-3c98743387a8"],
 StyleBox[" \[Rule] ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"a038252d-33e4-4652-b7f2-db59b645f264"],
 "\n\nIn principle a Lie algebra is not much more than that, it is a vector \
space with the additional structure of a product rule that takes any two \
elements of the vector space and returns a new vector space element. This \
product rule is often called a Lie bracket and denoted by ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[LeftDoubleBracket]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"8e809b59-e262-4cda-bf85-3a5b4fb91cc4"],
 " \[CenterDot], \[CenterDot]",
 StyleBox["\[RightDoubleBracket]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " . For our three-dimensional space, the cross product (",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[LeftDoubleBracket]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"82fd1873-4a08-4401-b172-02b81ef95b6f"],
 " \[CenterDot], \[CenterDot]\[RightDoubleBracket]",
 StyleBox[" = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[CenterDot]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"37826a2c-e921-469b-a092-f6ff11e73022"],
 StyleBox[" \[Times] \[CenterDot]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ") thus turns ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[DoubleStruckCapitalR]", "3"], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"06360831-5079-49d6-befd-04c3716609a8"],
 " from a vector space into a Lie algebra. \n"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.728220896380918*^9, 3.728221063488654*^9}, {
   3.7282211222267337`*^9, 3.728221130577482*^9}, {3.7282211686435347`*^9, 
   3.728221248183666*^9}, {3.728221349247451*^9, 3.7282214691937075`*^9}, {
   3.728221527829361*^9, 3.728221552814209*^9}, {3.7282216003270726`*^9, 
