   3.852200069619651*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"5b9b2e49-734e-43c7-adbf-\
5ab8586974d6"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Starting from an initial set of operators ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    SubscriptBox["Q", "1"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7f2c789f-cecd-4951-a628-b79917ef80a0"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["Q", "2"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "261a1542-15ff-47a6-bde7-4b609959ebec"],
 ", ...} the ",
 StyleBox["LieAlgebra ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "routine generates the corresponding Lie algebra through iterative \
application of standard Lie bracket (see background). The general syntax is \
given by:\n\n",
 StyleBox["LieAlgebra[",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"{", 
    SubscriptBox["Q", "1"]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"665ec2f4-fabc-4398-9bef-e47a40b3b163"],
 StyleBox[", ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["Q", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"a76efe6d-b333-4b7f-86c2-c25399c7c51e"],
 StyleBox[", ...}, opts]\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"where", " ", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     SubscriptBox["Q", "1"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Plain",ExpressionUUID->
  "7e3f57a2-b9e0-47b1-9e1c-18c58c354631"],
 ", ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["Q", "2"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Plain",ExpressionUUID->
  "b3a4a982-49df-44bb-8118-ea0867d2491c"],
 ", ...} refers to the initial set of operators and opts to any additional \
options. ",
 "\n\nA standard example is the Lie algebra so(3) of the three-dimensional \
rotation group. The Lie algebra so(3) may be generated from the following set \
of operators "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.728220896380918*^9, 3.728221063488654*^9}, {
