 Background->RGBColor[
  1, 0.925, 0.925],ExpressionUUID->"51a39fba-6d16-4382-8996-1a4fadd0739a"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The Schur-Weyl duality is a remarkable result from representation theory \
that relates the irreducible representations of the general linear group to \
the irreducible representations of the symmetric group in a unique way. \n\n\
For typical NMR applications however Schur-Weyl duality theorem is often much \
more powerful than needed. In very simple terms a generic NMR experiment \
consists of two ingredients: \n\n1) the spin Hamiltonian\n2) rotations in \
three-dimensional space\n\nThe spin Hamiltonian might possess some type of \
permutation symmetry, in example two strongly coupled spin-1/2 particles. As \
a consequence whatever pulse is applied to the system the two spins react \
identically. In other words in NMR experiments we do not care about relations \
between the general linear group and the symmetric group, but instead about \
relations between the three-dimensional rotation group and the symmetric \
group!\n\nTo illustrate the basic ideas we consider two identical spin-1/2 \
particles described by the Hamiltonian \n\nH = ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["\[Omega]", "0"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1ce53819-8a16-4251-b5ee-ab39180ff2e8"],
 "(",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["I", 
    RowBox[{"1", "z"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f103b095-7268-4331-ac8e-296697ce3c82"],
 "+",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["I", 
    RowBox[{"2", "z"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ef0019f6-98d1-4099-91f1-8560a33b1bef"],
 ") + 2\[Pi] J ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["I", "1"], "\[CenterDot]", 
    SubscriptBox["I", "2"]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f2d8b0d8-b69f-4d4d-bcb1-00d9a5e1e5bc"],
 "\n\nThe energy eigenstates of this Hamiltonian are the singlet state and \
the triplet states.\n\n",
 StyleBox["|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["S", "0"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"eec87b18-f1b8-41a7-a199-a3449b34fa26"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"376ac3a4-9e22-492c-a594-bb2c53876f9b"],
 StyleBox["(|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Alpha]\[Beta]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"9d5bd98f-f574-417f-971a-04a5aa19c8ea"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]-|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Beta]\[Alpha]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"9ffaadf2-00c9-4f3e-9907-d48f9df220bd"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]), |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", 
    RowBox[{"+", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"a4087abc-ea39-4976-bdf8-fc0749e74128"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] = |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Alpha]\[Alpha]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"d5b23a59-b914-41ba-bc44-dfc0af74edf1"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket], |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "0"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"380e44c7-ea68-45d9-b9a2-4594ff9b617b"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] = ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox["1", 
    SqrtBox["2"]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"e601303f-b4a7-47db-b86d-4e55874651b5"],
 StyleBox["(|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Alpha]\[Beta]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"d62d46f4-d001-4047-b16c-a882ea60c25b"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]+|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Beta]\[Alpha]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"b6776dfa-a8ff-401b-85f7-9b4e0026caf3"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]), |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", 
    RowBox[{"-", "1"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"f6545d69-03ad-4694-b317-ad7a13ad04c6"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] = |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["\[Beta]\[Beta]", TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"0630539f-7745-44db-812a-8dd4886d85e3"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "The triplet states are symmetric (",
 StyleBox["g",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ") w.r.t. permutation of spins 1 and 2, whereas the singlet state is \
anti-symmetric (",
 StyleBox["u",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ") under the same permutation.\n",
 StyleBox["\n(12)|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["S", "0"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"94177005-ec70-4428-9cd6-4d39069bc665"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]  = (-1) |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["S", "0"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"b98a806b-6240-4bb3-aca0-14e7d54ad006"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]\n(12)|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "m"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"4280ddd0-21d9-425a-97dd-734237dc7826"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] = (+1)|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "m"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"9d42fe7a-2d04-4f8b-82eb-181124d6b0d8"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket]  \n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "Similarly, the triplet states have total angular momentum of I=1 and \
transform among each other under rotations, whereas the singlet state has \
total angular momentum of I=0 and is rotationally invariant. The spin states \
thus have the following signatures:\n\n",
 StyleBox["|",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["S", "0"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"91fb8a82-c335-4c4d-b7b7-2f34d8c766c8"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] \[LeftRightArrow] (u, I=0) ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "and",
 StyleBox[" |",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["T", "m"], TraditionalForm]],
  FontWeight->"Bold",ExpressionUUID->"56839fbd-0c14-4936-92bd-7462fd934e1f"],
 StyleBox["\[RightAngleBracket] \[LeftRightArrow] (g, I=1)\n\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "The signatures highlight the fact that spin states with a given permutation \
symmetry have a well-defined rotational symmetry. This is part of the essence \
of the Schur-Weyl duality theorem. ",
 StyleBox["\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.728220896380918*^9, 3.728221063488654*^9}, {
